oai_dc:dc.dc:title: SEDIMENT MOVEMENT AT SOUTH INDIAN PORTS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Manohar, Madhav
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: sediment transport
ports
India
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The movement of sedimentary matter along the coastal regions of the land has always been a problem in coastal and harbour engineering. Erosion and accretion of the shore and the sea bottom and the silt charge from the rivers discharging into the sea contribute the necessary sediment that moves along the coast.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 6 (1957): Proceedings of 6th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Gainesville, Florida, 1957.; 22
